docs.abstract: Throngs of people poured into major thoroughfares for a march marking Human Rights Day.
docs.snippet: Throngs of people poured into major thoroughfares for a march marking Human Rights Day.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Hundreds of thousands of protesters, basking in a recent election victory by Hong Kong’s pro-democracy camp, poured onto the city’s streets on Sunday in one of the largest marches in weeks to pressure the government to meet demands for greater civil liberties.

headline.main: Hong Kong Protest, Largest in Weeks, Stretches Several Miles

docs.abstract: The A.C.L.U. asked the Supreme Court to hear an appeal from DeRay Mckesson, a Black Lives Matter activist sued by a Louisiana police officer.
docs.snippet: The A.C.L.U. asked the Supreme Court to hear an appeal from DeRay Mckesson, a Black Lives Matter activist sued by a Louisiana police officer.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The lawsuit, a federal judge found, bordered on the delusional. A Louisiana police officer injured in a protest tried to sue the hashtag #BlackLivesMatter, which amounted, wrote Judge Brian A. Jackson of the Federal District Court in Baton Rouge, to picking a fight with an idea. “A hashtag,” Judge Jackson wrote, “is patently incapable of being sued.”

docs.abstract: I dropped out of film school to edit video for the conspiracy theorist because I believed in his worldview. Then I saw what it did to people.
docs.snippet: I dropped out of film school to edit video for the conspiracy theorist because I believed in his worldview. Then I saw what it did to people.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Election Day 2016, I sat in the passenger seat of Alex Jones’s Dodge Hellcat as we swerved through traffic, making our way to a nearby polling place. As Jones punched the gas pedal to the floor, the smell of vodka, like paint thinner, wafted up from the white Dixie cup anchored in the console. My stomach churned as the phone I held streamed live video to Facebook: Jones rambling about voter fraud and rigged elections while I stared at the screen, holding the camera at an angle to hide his double chin. It rarely worked, but I didn’t want to be blamed when he watched the video later.

headline.main: I Worked for Alex Jones. I Regret It.

docs.abstract: Authoritarian and divisive polices of the Modi government have pushed Indians across the country to the streets in protest.
docs.snippet: Authoritarian and divisive polices of the Modi government have pushed Indians across the country to the streets in protest.
docs.lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — Prime Minister Narendra Modi of India and his Hindu nationalist Bharatiya Janata Party government have deployed propaganda very successfully since coming to power in 2014. So much so that numerous egregious decisions the government has made — demonetization, electoral bonds allowing secret donations to political parties, a flawed citizens registry in the state of Assam, revoking the autonomy of Jammu and Kashmir — were accepted by a majority of people.

headline.main: India Awakens to Fight for Its Soul

docs.abstract: The rise of China threatens the free world.
docs.snippet: The rise of China threatens the free world.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Carrie Lam, the lame-duck Beijing-backed ruler of Hong Kong, is unhappy that Christmas has been “ruined by a group of reckless and selfish rioters.” Joan Shang, who works in sustainable development and has joined the pro-democracy protests, takes a different view. “It’s an ideological war and we are at the center of it,” she said of the near-seven-month campaign. Such struggles do not take a break for Santa.

headline.main: The ‘Infinity War’ in the Streets of Hong Kong
headline.print_headline: The ‘Infinity War’ in the Streets of Hong Kong
